{
  "texts": [
    "However, studies have shown that people interacting with chatbots, like ChatGPT, tend to spend less time on search tasks compared to conventional web search engines (Xu et al., 2023).",
    "Therefore, we consider that task/search duration could be a valuable metric to assess how effectively our chatbot strategy promotes critical learning during conversational searches.",
    "We measured the search frequency, corresponding to the number of times the participants issued queries to the chatbots during their decision-making tasks.",
    "Similar to task/search duration, this metric is also often used to evaluate how willing people are to learn a topic in the fields of information retrieval and humancomputer interaction.",
    "The query issue count can be regarded as how the participants came up with questions in their minds while interacting with the chatbots for their decision-making."
  ]
}